Text: The sound of the piano grows nearer.

They call these tunnels an underground labyrinth,
but they feel more like ruins than a maze.
Rose comes upon a large set of demolished doors.
The music is coming from beyond.
Rose passes through a big hole in the doors...
and finally arrives.

It is a temple illuminated from above by a
phantasmal light.
Colorful light pours through the windows.
You're...
Shadow...

He is alone, playing "Moonlight Sonata" here in this
forgotten place of worship.

But the way he plays the song is different from all
the other renditions Rose had heard before now.

The face of a song can change depending on who
performs it.
And Shadow's "Moonlight Sonata" is darkness.

The deep, deep darkness of night, pierced by but a
single ray of light.
Was it the light of the moon, or perhaps...

The song reaches its end before Rose can find the
answer to this question.

Rose savors the last of the trailing notes echoing
through the chamber, then claps.

That was undoubtedly the best performance of
"Moonlight Sonata" I've ever heard.
What is it you seek...?
I wanted to protect everyone...
But...I couldn't.
And is this where it ends...?
Huh...?
Is this where your battle ends...?
I didn't want things to end here like this!
I wanted to take hold of the best possible future!

She wanted to do something, still wants to even now.
But she no longer has it in her power to do anything.
If you possess the will to fight...

Bluish-purple magic gathers in Shadow's palm as he
speaks.
I shall grant you power.

The energy grows even brighter, painting the chamber
in its dazzling hues and causing the air to tremble
under its weight.
Will this power allow me to change the future...?
That all depends upon you.

Rose notices herself growing captivated by the
bluish-purple glow of the magic.
If she had strength like Shadow's...
Fire returns to her eyes.
There is something I must do as a princess of Oriana!
A wish I must safeguard as Rose Oriana!
And in order to do so, I will need power!!!
The bluish-purple magic flows forth.
This is...

The warm force calms the rampaging magic within her,
restoring it to order.

What had once been somehow too
heavy to control is now light and moves as she
wishes.

Even the black welts of the possession vanish in
the blink of an eye.
Incredible...
She means it with all her heart.
This is your magic.
The world as you see it.
Revolt.
Prove that you have the will to fight.

The next thing she knows, Shadow is nowhere to
be seen.
Only his voice echoes in the temple.
Do not forget.
True strength does not come from power...
but from the way you live your life.

And then she no longer senses Shadow's presence.
Rose is alone in the hall.
She feels those hunting her arrive.
Feeling the chill in the air....
A magic unlike any before swirls in her body.

She had thought that it would be best to be caught.
But now, with this power...there is still more she can
do.
Rose draws her rapier.
That robe... Are you from the Cult of Diablos?

The fact that you choose now of all times to show
yourselves can only mean one thing...

In the next moment, a troop of figures dressed in
black appear.
Blades take aim at Rose, intent on claiming her head.
However...
Sprays of blood fill the air.

Her assailants are cut down before they even
notice her own drawn steel.

In a temple that is now stained red, Rose sheathes
her blade.

Shadow's own battles must have gone similarly,
an ongoing struggle unseen by all.

Rose thinks of his performance of "Moonlight Sonata"
once more.

Shadow... He is the ray of moonlight shining through
the darkness.
And if all goes as I wish...I shall be, too.
